Former president Thabo Mbeki has been named the University of South Africa s new Chancellor, the university said in a statement on Thursday. Mbeki s appointment follows the retirement of Judge Bernard Ngoepe from a role he held for 15 years. According to eNCA, Unisa explained that Mbeki was selected, following a rigorous selection process, because of his role as an intellectual giant in Africa and his contribution to African Renaissance. The university, in welcoming Mbeki, further said it hoped the former statesman s role would add more value to the university. Adding to this was vice chancellor Mandla Makhanya, who also welcomed Mbeki to the new role and expressed excitement at the contribution the former president would make to the university. Details on Mbeki&#8217;s inauguration are yet to be announced. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.